## üîß Deployment Instructions

### Quick Setup
1. Copy all files to your GitHub repository
2. Ensure file names match exactly (case-sensitive)
3. Deploy to your preferred hosting platform
4. Test on mobile devices and different browsers

### GitHub Repository Setup
```bash
# Clone your repository
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd <your-repo-name>

# Copy the files
# - index.html
# - styles.css
# - script.js
# - sw.js
# - manifest.json

# Commit and push
git add .
git commit -m "Add LockGram professional landing page"
git push origin main
```

### Hosting Recommendations
- **Vercel**: Automatic deployments from GitHub
- **Netlify**: Easy setup with custom domains
- **GitHub Pages**: Free hosting for public repos
- **Cloudflare Pages**: Global CDN with security features

